            <title>Owens Corning Awarded Green Cross for Safety Medal</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;img alt="" src="http://media.noria.com/sites/Uploads/2014/4/15/0b3f698c-63fe-48ff-830e-356f1245c21c_owens-corning-2.jpeg" style="width: 220px; height: 176px; margin: 7px; float: left;" /&gt;The National Safety Council recently presented Owens Corning with the Green Cross for Safety medal at its 15th annual fundraising dinner in Atlanta. The dinner honored Owens Corning for its steadfast commitment to improving safety and health in the workplace and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;Receiving the Green Cross for Safety medal honors the dedication of all of our employees,&amp;quot; said Michael H. Thaman, Owens Corning chairman and CEO. &amp;quot;We lead from safety, which means our ability to execute on safety is a primary indicator of how we perform as a company.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
