            <title>OSHA Announces Top 10 Safety Violations</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	The Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) recently announced the top 10 most-cited workplace safety violations at the 2013 National Safety Council Congress and Expo in Chicago. Once again, fall protection topped the list with 8,241 violations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We appreciate our colleagues at OSHA sharing their most recent data as we look toward leading safety into the future,&amp;quot; said National Safety Council president and CEO Janet Froetscher. &amp;quot;Today&amp;#39;s presentation reminds us that it&amp;#39;s very important to learn from the past and address these top violations to help make our workplaces safer.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Hazard communication was second on the list of top violations, followed by scaffolding, respiratory protection, electrical/wiring methods, powered industrial trucks and ladders. Rounding out the top 10 were lockout/tagout, electrical/general requirements and machine guarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The preliminary figures for the 2013 fiscal year are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Standard&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Total Violations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	1.&amp;nbsp; 1926.501 &amp;ndash; Fall Protection &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;8,241&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	2.&amp;nbsp; 1910.1200 &amp;ndash; Hazard Communication &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 6,156&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	3.&amp;nbsp; 1926.451 &amp;ndash; Scaffolding &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 5,423&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	4.&amp;nbsp; 1910.134 &amp;ndash; Respiratory Protection &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;3,879&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	5.&amp;nbsp; 1910.305 &amp;ndash; Electrical, Wiring Methods &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 3,452&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	6.&amp;nbsp; 1910.178 &amp;ndash; Powered Industrial Trucks &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;3,340&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	7.&amp;nbsp; 1926.1053 &amp;ndash; Ladders &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 3,311&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	8.&amp;nbsp; 1910.147 &amp;ndash; Lockout/Tagout &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;3,254&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	9.&amp;nbsp; 1910.303 &amp;ndash; Electrical, General Requirements &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 2,745&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	10. 1910.212 &amp;ndash; Machine Guarding &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 2,701&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://nsc.org"&gt;nsc.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/workplace_safety/~4/1lAgtJKe5Fs" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
