            <title>4 Hypertherm Facilities Recognized as 'Star' Worksites for Safety</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	The United States Department of Labor recently recognized four Hypertherm facilities as &amp;quot;star&amp;quot; worksites as part of the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Voluntary Protection Program (VPP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The VPP star program recognizes the nation&amp;rsquo;s best workplaces for operating outstanding safety and health management systems for employee protection. It is OSHA&amp;rsquo;s official recognition of the outstanding efforts of employers and employees who have created exemplary worksite safety and health management systems. These worksites are self-sufficient in identifying and controlling workplace hazards. To be recognized as a VPP star worksite, an employer must operate a comprehensive safety and health management system that is integrated into a worksite&amp;rsquo;s operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The latest four facilities to be recognized join two other Hypertherm worksites that have received OSHA&amp;rsquo;s VPP star designation. Hypertherm&amp;rsquo;s recognition as having multiple star worksites is based on an integrated management system&amp;rsquo;s approach to health and safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;The cornerstone of our program is Hypertherm&amp;rsquo;s culture, which promotes associate involvement and teamwork at all levels of our organization,&amp;quot; said Hypertherm founder and CEO Dick Couch. &amp;quot;All team members work together to design workplace enhancements that will improve the overall well-being of all Hypertherm associates with an ultimate goal of zero workplace accidents.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Based in Hanover, N.H., Hypertherm designs and manufactures advanced cutting products for use in a variety of industries such as ship building, manufacturing and automotive repair. For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.hypertherm.com"&gt;www.hypertherm.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/workplace_safety/~4/eSpInkZJn1E" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
